When you run:

bash
Copy
Edit
oc apply -f inject-cert-ds.yaml
OpenShift schedules a pod on each node, and it mounts /etc, injects your ca.crt, and runs update-ca-trust.

âœ… Steps to Proceed (from bdgtr076x11t1)
ðŸ”¸ Create the ConfigMap (run this once):

bash
Copy
Edit
oc create configmap registry-cert \
  --from-file=ca.crt=/opt/registry/certs/domain.crt \
  -n openshift-config
ðŸ”¸ Save the below DaemonSet YAML as inject-cert-ds.yaml:

yaml
Copy
Edit
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: DaemonSet
metadata:
  name: inject-registry-cert
  namespace: openshift-config
spec:
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      name: inject-registry-cert
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        name: inject-registry-cert
    spec:
      hostPID: true
      hostNetwork: true
      tolerations:
      - operator: "Exists"
      containers:
      - name: install-cert
        image: registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8/ubi:latest
        command: ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
        args:
        - |
          mkdir -p /host/etc/docker/certs.d/sd-wv58-kflz.nam.nsroot.net:5000
          cp /certs/ca.crt /host/etc/docker/certs.d/sd-wv58-kflz.nam.nsroot.net:5000/ca.crt
          chroot /host update-ca-trust extract || true
          sleep 300
        volumeMounts:
        - name: certs
          mountPath: /certs
        - name: host-etc
          mountPath: /host/etc
      volumes:
      - name: certs
        configMap:
          name: registry-cert
      - name: host-etc
        hostPath:
          path: /etc
ðŸ”¸ Apply the DaemonSet:

bash
Copy
Edit
oc apply -f inject-cert-ds.yaml
ðŸ”¸ Monitor and validate:

bash
Copy
Edit
